HEADWORD: Miniver
<hw>Min"i*ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Meniver</er>.]</ety> <def>A fur esteemed in the Middle Ages as a
part of costume. It is uncertain whether it was the fur of one animal
only or of different animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

